'''ᱟᱠᱷᱤᱞ ᱟᱠᱠᱤᱱᱮᱱᱤ''' (born 8 April 1994) is an American<!-- THIS REFERS TO HIS CITIZENSHIP, not ethnicity/origin. DO NOT CHANGE HIS NATIONALITY. His Indian origin is already mentioned in this page. --> actor of Indian origin<ref name="Birthplace" /> who predominantly works in [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-language films.

== Personal Life ==
Akhil Akkineni is the son of actors [[Akkineni Nagarjuna|Nagarjuna]] and [[Amala (actress)|Amala]], the grandson of actor [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao|Nageswara Rao]], and half-brother of [[Naga Chaitanya]]. His sister-in-law [[Samantha Akkineni|Samantha]] is also an actor. Akkineni pursued acting at the [[Lee Strasberg Theatre and Film Institute]] before making his debut in films in 2014 through a cameo in ''[[Manam (film)|Manam]]''. His first film in a lead role came in ''[[Akhil (film)|Akhil]]'' (2015).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/I-was-mobbed-by-girls-a-few-times-Akhil/articleshow/46252275.cms|title=I was mobbed by girls a few times: Akhil|work=The Times of India}}</ref> In 2016, Akkineni was engaged to Shriya Bhupal, grand daughter of business tycoon [[G. V. Krishna Reddy]]. Their wedding was planned in 2017 but was later called off.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2017-02-23|title=Real reason why Nagarjuna’s son Akhil Akkineni, Shriya Bhupal called off wedding?|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/real-reason-why-nagarjuna-son-akhil-akkineni-shriya-bhupal-called-off-wedding-4539732/|access-date=2020-07-07|website=The Indian Express|language=en}}</ref>

==Education==
Akkineni studied at Chaitanya Vidyalaya, later headed to Australia for two years. He returned to complete his studies at [[Oakridge International School]], [[Hyderabad]]. He pursued acting as a career at age 16 and enrolled in an acting course at the [[Lee Strasberg Theatre and Film Institute]] in New York.
He is a [[BBA]] graduate from [[University of South Florida]]
